WEBVTT

00:02.380 --> 00:03.580
Katie: You did it, Katie.

00:03.580 --> 00:04.880
You made it through the summer.

00:04.880 --> 00:06.120
Taylor: Mom!
Oliver: Mom?

00:06.120 --> 00:07.500
These kids have been
up in your face

00:07.500 --> 00:09.670
for 68 days in a row.

00:09.670 --> 00:11.750
And now you get to place them
in the custody

00:11.750 --> 00:13.330
of the Westport
public school system.

00:13.330 --> 00:14.460
Anna-Kat: Mom!
Mom!

00:14.460 --> 00:15.380
Mom! Where are you?

00:15.380 --> 00:16.670
It's like you're a warden,

00:16.670 --> 00:17.790
and you're transferring
these delinquents

00:17.790 --> 00:19.000
to another prison.

00:19.000 --> 00:20.500
All you have to do is
get them there.

00:20.500 --> 00:21.540
Let's do this.

00:21.540 --> 00:23.330
[ Footsteps approaching ]

00:23.330 --> 00:24.380
Mom, a word.

00:24.380 --> 00:25.250
No words.

00:25.250 --> 00:26.120
We've gotta get
to school.

00:26.120 --> 00:27.380
Mom --
No.

00:27.380 --> 00:28.670
But I didn't even ask
anything yet.

00:28.670 --> 00:31.290
It's either too expensive
or I don't have time.

00:31.290 --> 00:33.120
Mom?
You cannot have a dog.

00:33.120 --> 00:35.210
You didn't swear this time!
You're softening.

00:35.210 --> 00:36.210
Greg!

00:36.210 --> 00:38.380
Can you help me
find my car keys?

00:38.380 --> 00:40.620
How do you manage
to constantly misplace --

00:40.620 --> 00:42.170
There's probably a better time
for that talk.

00:42.170 --> 00:43.580
I'll help you look.

00:43.580 --> 00:46.250
Mom, I got another run
in my tights.

00:46.250 --> 00:48.040
I'm in a real
ballet academy now.

00:48.040 --> 00:50.830
For God's sake, buy a boy
a decent pair of Danskins!

00:50.830 --> 00:53.080
Mom...
Mom, my driver's license test
is in two weeks,

00:53.080 --> 00:54.500
and I need someone
to take me out to practice.

00:54.500 --> 00:55.960
Can't drive
without car keys.

00:55.960 --> 00:57.750
Everyone fan out.

00:57.750 --> 01:00.210
Mom, I need to look
professional.

01:00.210 --> 01:02.420
My plan of getting into Harvard
through ballet could be lost,

01:02.420 --> 01:04.290
all for the want
of a proper leotard.

01:04.290 --> 01:05.500
Well, my plan
for smoking cigarettes

01:05.500 --> 01:07.170
and eating takeout every night
was ruined by you,

01:07.170 --> 01:08.380
so we're even.

01:08.380 --> 01:11.210
I need you to take this
seriously.

01:11.210 --> 01:12.830
My teacher has already
taken an instant

01:12.830 --> 01:14.170
and strong dislike
to me.

01:14.170 --> 01:15.670
What happened
to my little boy

01:15.670 --> 01:17.540
with the beautiful
little girl's voice?

01:17.540 --> 01:18.710
Eh.

01:18.710 --> 01:20.460
-Mom.
-Mom!
-What?!

01:20.460 --> 01:24.330
Look at this picture
of a corgi dressed as a banana!

01:24.330 --> 01:25.830
Eh.

01:25.830 --> 01:27.830
Don't play me.
You know it's cute.

01:27.830 --> 01:29.710
Have you picked
your after-school activity yet?

01:29.710 --> 01:31.420
I told you,
I'm not doing one.

01:31.420 --> 01:32.460
Greg!

01:35.710 --> 01:37.380
Greg: Anna-Kat,
it's fun to be involved.

01:37.380 --> 01:39.210
Now that school's started,
I can't wait to be part

01:39.210 --> 01:41.250
of the recycling committee again
and hang with my crew.

01:41.250 --> 01:42.290
You mean the janitors?

01:42.290 --> 01:43.580
And Bill Doty.

01:43.580 --> 01:45.460
You guys,
worst fan-out of all time.

01:45.460 --> 01:47.250
Look for my keys in a place
that I'm not already looking.

01:50.290 --> 01:51.830
Taylor, do you got
your summer packet?

01:51.830 --> 01:54.040
Yeah, I have it.
I just didn't do it.

01:54.040 --> 01:55.920
You realize you're talking
to the mean parent, right?

01:55.920 --> 01:57.250
Just hear me out.

01:57.250 --> 01:59.960
I've decided...
I'm not going to college.

02:01.670 --> 02:03.120
Greg!

02:06.380 --> 02:07.460
Taylor, you are
going to college --

02:07.460 --> 02:09.460
probably not a good college,
but college.

02:09.460 --> 02:10.830
I just don't think
it's right for me.

02:10.830 --> 02:12.580
I mean, it's a waste
of my time and your money.

02:12.580 --> 02:13.880
Well, that's not
your call to make.

02:13.880 --> 02:15.170
So, until you finish
your summer packet,

02:15.170 --> 02:16.380
you're not gonna
start driving.

02:16.380 --> 02:17.790
Katie: Hold up!

02:17.790 --> 02:19.620
[ Laughing ] Greg.

02:19.620 --> 02:21.170
Stop fooling around.

02:21.170 --> 02:23.380
Of course you're gonna
start driving.

02:23.380 --> 02:25.080
And your father's
going to teach you.

02:25.080 --> 02:26.580
Can you go put
on a shirt

02:26.580 --> 02:29.460
that doesn't look like
it's Hooter-issued?

02:29.460 --> 02:31.790
And look for my keys.

02:31.790 --> 02:33.170
Whatever happened to
"never overruling

02:33.170 --> 02:34.330
one another
in front of the kids"?

02:34.330 --> 02:36.620
You are ruining
my master plan.

02:36.620 --> 02:37.710
Master plans are
for villains

02:37.710 --> 02:39.380
in the superhero movies
you drag me to,

02:39.380 --> 02:41.040
claiming the art-house films
I want to see

02:41.040 --> 02:42.920
are somehow always playing
at "bad times."

02:42.920 --> 02:45.620
You do not understand
my carpool schedule this year.

02:45.620 --> 02:48.500
At 2:45, I pick up
Oliver and Anna-Kat from school.

02:48.500 --> 02:50.830
Then I drive Oliver all the way
to Norwalk for ballet lessons

02:50.830 --> 02:52.380
and wait in the car
with Anna-Kat

02:52.380 --> 02:54.330
for 40 minutes,
playing "I Spy."

02:54.330 --> 02:56.250
Then I pick up Oliver again
and go all the way back

02:56.250 --> 02:57.960
to pick Taylor up
from volleyball

02:57.960 --> 02:59.330
and then drive
everyone home.

02:59.330 --> 03:01.290
So, I have
a three-pronged plan.

03:01.290 --> 03:03.710
Prong one --
Get Anna-Kat into a club

03:03.710 --> 03:05.620
so Taylor and her can be
on the same schedule.

03:05.620 --> 03:07.420
Prong two --
Oliver's ballet teacher

03:07.420 --> 03:09.620
breaks his spirits --
fingers crossed --

03:09.620 --> 03:11.330
he quits, joins baseball,
and the three of them

03:11.330 --> 03:13.250
are on the same schedule
at the same time.

03:13.250 --> 03:14.670
And prong three?
Here's prong three.

03:14.670 --> 03:15.920
Ready for prong three?
You know it.

03:15.920 --> 03:17.420
When Taylor gets
her license,

03:17.420 --> 03:19.380
she can drive them
to school and back.

03:19.380 --> 03:21.880
And then I'm free!

03:21.880 --> 03:23.290
Do you hear me, Greg?

03:23.290 --> 03:24.830
Free!
Chest hairs, Katie.

03:24.830 --> 03:26.830
And then I can take a step back
from mothering,

03:26.830 --> 03:30.040
finally enjoy my life
and pursue some hobbies,

03:30.040 --> 03:32.540
like sitting in the bathtub
with a glass of wine.

03:32.540 --> 03:33.920
Is that --
It's a hobby!

03:33.920 --> 03:35.040
Look it up.

03:35.040 --> 03:36.580
Anna-Kat:
I found your keys!

03:37.960 --> 03:39.040
Where were they?

03:39.040 --> 03:40.420
Right there.

03:40.420 --> 03:43.040
Who hung my keys
on the hook?

03:43.040 --> 03:44.750
How am I supposed to find
anything around this house

03:44.750 --> 03:46.960
if people put things
back where they belong?

03:52.880 --> 03:54.830
♪♪

03:54.830 --> 03:57.790
Anna-Kat, I need you to pick
a club from this list.

03:57.790 --> 04:00.330
It's important to be
involved in school.

04:00.330 --> 04:02.290
If it's so important,
how come you're not involved?

04:02.290 --> 04:04.790
She makes
an interesting point.

04:04.790 --> 04:06.540
Is this payback
for overruling you?

04:06.540 --> 04:07.960
Yes.
Okay.

04:07.960 --> 04:10.040
Tell you what,
I'll get involved if you do.

04:10.040 --> 04:11.380
Really?

04:11.380 --> 04:12.620
You're going to volunteer
at school like

04:12.620 --> 04:15.330
"all those no-life,
busy-body, idiot moms"?

04:15.330 --> 04:16.830
Yep.

04:16.830 --> 04:18.960
Right after I start watching
how I speak in front of you.

04:18.960 --> 04:27.040
♪♪

04:27.040 --> 04:30.250
I am here to volunteer.

04:33.120 --> 04:35.210
Maybe it's best
I start small.

04:35.210 --> 04:36.620
Ziploc Committee?

04:36.620 --> 04:37.960
Bring Ziplocs...

04:37.960 --> 04:42.040
Maybe the cute little
snack-sized ones.

04:42.040 --> 04:44.250
To hold snacks.

04:44.250 --> 04:45.830
What are you
doing here?

04:45.830 --> 04:47.040
Last year, you pretended
to be pregnant

04:47.040 --> 04:48.460
to get out
of volunteering.

04:48.460 --> 04:50.380
You are still hung up
on my fake pregnancy?

04:50.380 --> 04:52.920
You let me throw you
a baby shower.

04:52.920 --> 04:54.920
And took the gifts.
That's a lie.
Sage, you're a liar.

04:54.920 --> 04:57.540
You're using the diaper bag
I gave you as a purse.

05:01.960 --> 05:03.330
Katie, just go away.

05:03.330 --> 05:05.250
Your volunteer hours
are no good here.

05:05.250 --> 05:06.330
I don't get it.

05:06.330 --> 05:08.210
You guys forgave
Stacy Clouser,

05:08.210 --> 05:09.830
and I heard
at the Spring Gala

05:09.830 --> 05:11.620
that she attacked you all
with a crab claw

05:11.620 --> 05:13.670
and said she hoped all
your real noses grow back.

05:13.670 --> 05:15.000
Well,
that was different.

05:15.000 --> 05:16.540
She was having
a nervous breakdown

05:16.540 --> 05:18.170
from being
the Gala Chairperson.

05:18.170 --> 05:20.670
She had to move back in
with her parents.

05:20.670 --> 05:23.000
She has to wear tube socks
taped to her hands.

05:23.000 --> 05:24.880
Oh, and you can tell Greg

05:24.880 --> 05:26.580
he's no longer
on the recycling committee.

05:26.580 --> 05:27.620
Why?

05:27.620 --> 05:28.830
What did he do wrong?

05:28.830 --> 05:30.670
Married you.

05:30.670 --> 05:32.080
[ All giggle ]

05:32.080 --> 05:35.620
Sage, I have seen how hot
your babysitter is.

05:35.620 --> 05:37.380
It's only
a matter of time.

05:37.380 --> 05:41.290
♪♪

05:41.290 --> 05:43.170
You got me kicked off
the recycling committee?!

05:43.170 --> 05:44.710
Recycling
isn't even real, Greg!

05:44.710 --> 05:46.120
They make you separate
all your stuff

05:46.120 --> 05:47.580
and then dump it all together
in the same landfill.

05:47.580 --> 05:48.580
Don't say that!

05:48.580 --> 05:50.000
You promised
you'd never say that again!

05:51.830 --> 05:52.830
I just got an e-mail
with the roster

05:52.830 --> 05:54.080
for the next recital.

05:54.080 --> 05:55.880
My teacher's not
dancing me.

05:55.880 --> 05:57.670
I'm not getting
danced!

05:57.670 --> 05:59.000
How am I supposed
to get into Harvard

05:59.000 --> 06:00.210
if I'm riding the pine?

06:00.210 --> 06:02.080
Maybe she knows that
you don't love ballet

06:02.080 --> 06:03.670
and you're there
for the wrong reasons.

06:03.670 --> 06:06.880
You know what I love?
Recycling!

06:06.880 --> 06:08.710
How'd you miss that?

06:08.710 --> 06:10.210
How many times do I have
to tell everyone in this house?

06:10.210 --> 06:11.710
I have
an overly-round eye.

06:11.710 --> 06:13.380
Hey, you're not the only one
going through something.

06:13.380 --> 06:15.580
They banned me
from volunteering at school.

06:15.580 --> 06:17.000
They did? Great.

06:17.000 --> 06:19.080
That means I don't have
to join a club!

06:19.080 --> 06:21.080
My master plan
just went to hell.

06:21.080 --> 06:23.710
I'm gonna be spending
most of my life in my car.

06:23.710 --> 06:26.380
"Katie, let's get married
and start a family."

06:26.380 --> 06:27.880
"You know what, Greg,
I'm flattered, but no."

06:27.880 --> 06:29.120
Coulda said that.

06:33.420 --> 06:35.120
I was sure Stacy Clouser
going bonkers would've

06:35.120 --> 06:36.750
knocked my fake pregnancy
off the front page.

06:36.750 --> 06:39.170
I was at the Gala,
saw the whole thing.

06:39.170 --> 06:40.380
It was awesome.

06:40.380 --> 06:42.880
She was yelling
at the seafood tower,

06:42.880 --> 06:46.040
then pausing,
like it was yelling back.

06:46.040 --> 06:47.330
[ Laughs ]
[ Sighs ]

06:47.330 --> 06:49.460
Prong one of my plan
is falling apart.

06:49.460 --> 06:50.920
I got to get Anna-Kat
into a club,

06:50.920 --> 06:52.250
and to do that,

06:52.250 --> 06:54.170
those moms need
to let me volunteer.

06:54.170 --> 06:56.080
Doris, you used to work
in crisis management, right?

06:56.080 --> 06:58.620
I did.
I called myself "The Fixer."

06:58.620 --> 07:00.500
Couldn't get anyone else
to do it.

07:00.500 --> 07:02.420
It was the one thing
The Fixer couldn't fix.

07:02.420 --> 07:04.080
So fix me.
What can I do?

07:04.080 --> 07:05.790
Okay, uh...
first step --

07:05.790 --> 07:06.960
gain sympathy.

07:06.960 --> 07:08.080
You check into rehab.

07:08.080 --> 07:09.620
-Mm.
-Uh, no.

07:09.620 --> 07:11.620
Okay...
Say your stepfather hit you.

07:11.620 --> 07:12.790
Or stepmother.

07:12.790 --> 07:14.790
A woman can be
just as abusive as a man.

07:14.790 --> 07:17.830
Weird moment for feminism,
Angela.

07:17.830 --> 07:19.540
Okay. Well, then,
all that's left is the Internet.

07:19.540 --> 07:22.210
Make a public apology video
like the celebrities do.
Yeah.

07:22.210 --> 07:24.750
Be all sad
and remorseful.

07:24.750 --> 07:26.460
Well, it's either
humiliating myself

07:26.460 --> 07:28.500
or driving around with Anna-Kat
all afternoon.

07:28.500 --> 07:30.250
I spy with my little eye --

07:30.250 --> 07:32.790
The stain on the back
of the seat.

07:32.790 --> 07:34.960
How did you know?

07:34.960 --> 07:38.920
It's always the stain
on the back of the seat.

07:38.920 --> 07:40.710
Let's make that video.

07:40.710 --> 07:42.580
Hi, guys --
Doris: Too peppy.

07:42.580 --> 07:44.380
You're gonna have to look
more remorseful.

07:44.380 --> 07:46.380
Can you cry?

07:46.380 --> 07:47.380
No.

07:47.380 --> 07:49.250
Angela,
make some tears.

07:49.250 --> 07:50.880
Oka-- All right.
Okay.

07:50.880 --> 07:52.830
Okay. Let's just...

07:52.830 --> 07:55.920
Okay. And...action.

07:55.920 --> 07:59.170
Ladies of
the volunteer committee.

07:59.170 --> 08:03.250
I am taking this opportunity
to say...

08:03.250 --> 08:04.170
Cut!

08:04.170 --> 08:05.460
Doris:
What's the problem?

08:05.460 --> 08:07.830
I am not comparing myself
to Hitler.

08:07.830 --> 08:09.710
I wrote
"Hitler of Westport."

08:09.710 --> 08:12.080
That's different from
Hitler Hitler.

08:12.080 --> 08:13.920
Recreational
paint huffer?
Yes.

08:13.920 --> 08:15.710
You know what? I'm not
saying any of this stuff.

08:15.710 --> 08:17.080
I'm just going to be
straightforward.

08:17.080 --> 08:18.040
Press the button.

08:18.040 --> 08:19.500
[ Camera beeps ]

08:19.500 --> 08:20.460
[ Sighs ]

08:20.460 --> 08:21.750
Hey, guys.

08:21.750 --> 08:23.500
I messed up.

08:23.500 --> 08:25.080
I hope that you can forgive me.

08:25.080 --> 08:27.000
Especially you, Suzanne.

08:27.000 --> 08:28.920
Not so much you, Tara.

08:28.920 --> 08:32.460
Anyway, I'm super-sorry
that I faked being pregnant

08:32.460 --> 08:35.000
and I exchanged
the bassinet you gave me

08:35.000 --> 08:36.880
for a margarita machine.

08:36.880 --> 08:38.670
Now say you have
Lyme Disease.

08:38.670 --> 08:41.750
I'm not saying
I have Lyme Disease.

08:41.750 --> 08:44.620
No Lyme Disease, no Hitler --
Do you hear yourself?!

08:44.620 --> 08:46.380
Greg: We'll go the abandoned
Circuit City in Norwalk

08:46.380 --> 08:48.080
so you can practice driving
in the parking lot.

08:48.080 --> 08:49.790
To avoid danger,
you always have to be aware

08:49.790 --> 08:53.250
of what's ahead of you,
both on the road and in life...

08:53.250 --> 08:55.540
like a college education,
for instance.

08:55.540 --> 08:58.040
Dad, it just doesn't
make sense for me.

08:58.040 --> 08:59.880
Or for you.
How so?

08:59.880 --> 09:02.420
You really want to have to pay
three college tuitions?

09:02.420 --> 09:04.000
Oliver's getting
a dance scholarship.

09:04.000 --> 09:07.000
No. He's using ballet
to get into Harvard.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.210
No one said anything
about a scholarship.

09:09.210 --> 09:13.460
You're going to be on the hook
for like $500,000.

09:13.460 --> 09:15.290
You're not looking
at what's ahead.

09:15.290 --> 09:16.210
I guess I wasn't.

09:16.210 --> 09:17.330
No. Dad!

09:17.330 --> 09:18.500
Oh, God!

09:18.500 --> 09:20.620
[ Tires screech ]

09:20.620 --> 09:23.290
[ Car door opens ]

09:23.290 --> 09:26.540
Aww, he held on to
his little flag. [ Chuckles ]

09:26.540 --> 09:29.920
[ Somber music playing ]
Anyhow, I'm super-sorry
that I faked being pregnant

09:29.920 --> 09:32.040
and that I exchanged
that bassinet you gave me

09:32.040 --> 09:34.040
for a margarita machine.

09:34.040 --> 09:35.790
I have Lyme Disease.

09:35.790 --> 09:38.670
[ Tear drop splashes ]

09:38.670 --> 09:40.120
This is terrible.

09:40.120 --> 09:42.210
You left me no choice!
Look at your face.

09:42.210 --> 09:43.920
It didn't look apologetic
at all.

09:43.920 --> 09:46.380
Why didn't you show it to me
before you posted it?

09:46.380 --> 09:48.460
I thought you're supposed to be
good at what you did!

09:48.460 --> 09:50.170
Uh, thinking about it now,

09:50.170 --> 09:51.710
I'm not sure if I quit my job
to have kids

09:51.710 --> 09:54.170
or if I got fired
then decided to have kids.

09:54.170 --> 09:55.750
[ Doorbell rings ]
[ Sighs ]

09:55.750 --> 09:57.080
Just great.

09:57.080 --> 09:58.460
You don't get back in
with the moms,

09:58.460 --> 09:59.880
and I don't get back
on the recycling committee.

09:59.880 --> 10:02.290
Who's going to make sure all the
cans and jars are rinsed out?

10:02.290 --> 10:04.290
Nobody,
because it's nonsense, Greg.

10:04.290 --> 10:06.460
It's right up there with
washing fruit before you eat it.

10:09.540 --> 10:11.170
Suzanne.

10:11.170 --> 10:13.540
I saw your video
on Facebook.

10:13.540 --> 10:15.620
Can we talk?

10:15.620 --> 10:20.040
This is hard for me,
because I'm a nice person.

10:20.040 --> 10:22.120
Yeah, and I, too,
am a Lyme's survivor.

10:22.120 --> 10:23.170
Hmm.

10:23.170 --> 10:24.960
[ Sighs ]

10:24.960 --> 10:26.880
The reason you feel
like you don't fit in

10:26.880 --> 10:28.500
with me and the other moms

10:28.500 --> 10:32.120
has nothing to do with us
and everything to do with you.

10:32.120 --> 10:33.960
You don't want
to fit in.

10:33.960 --> 10:35.290
I don't think
that's true.

10:35.290 --> 10:36.830
You're constantly
mocking us

10:36.830 --> 10:39.460
for being healthy and active
and involved at school

10:39.460 --> 10:42.000
when, Katie, those are
all very normal things.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.170
Suzanne --
No, let me finish.

10:44.170 --> 10:46.380
You think that you're the one
who's being judged,

10:46.380 --> 10:48.750
but you're the one, Katie,
who's doing all the judging --

10:48.750 --> 10:50.540
You.

10:50.540 --> 10:53.000
You're the one
who looks down on us.

10:55.460 --> 11:02.540
♪♪

11:02.540 --> 11:03.710
You don't wash our fruit?!

11:08.290 --> 11:10.580
Suzanne says that
I look down on them.

11:10.580 --> 11:12.580
I'm the snob?

11:12.580 --> 11:14.080
The nicest thing that I own
is a purse

11:14.080 --> 11:16.380
that's actually a diaper bag
that I had to steal.

11:16.380 --> 11:18.620
How dare she!
Can you believe she said that?

11:18.620 --> 11:19.960
Sex on the table
tonight?

11:19.960 --> 11:21.540
No.

11:21.540 --> 11:23.000
Well, you do kind of
judge people

11:23.000 --> 11:25.380
for what some might consider
admirable behavior,

11:25.380 --> 11:28.250
like eating healthy,
exercising, recycling.

11:28.250 --> 11:30.290
We should go
to a recycling plant.

11:30.290 --> 11:32.380
I hear that they let unicorns
lead the tours.

11:32.380 --> 11:33.670
You know what?

11:33.670 --> 11:34.750
We're not gonna talk
about recycling.

11:34.750 --> 11:36.670
It's too hot a topic.

11:36.670 --> 11:38.290
How are you doing
with Taylor's driving?

11:38.290 --> 11:39.540
Um...

11:39.540 --> 11:40.620
Shouldn't you be
more concerned

11:40.620 --> 11:42.210
about Taylor not wanting
to go to college

11:42.210 --> 11:43.380
than learning how
to drive?

11:43.380 --> 11:44.540
If Taylor doesn't learn
how to drive,

11:44.540 --> 11:46.790
then my master plan
is going out the window.

11:46.790 --> 11:50.000
Greg, if I have to keep driving
as much as I do, I swear --

11:50.000 --> 11:51.170
[ Tires screeching,
heroic music playing ]

11:51.170 --> 11:52.750
[ Music trails off, splash ]

11:52.750 --> 11:54.500
Well, at least your car
will be clean.

11:54.500 --> 11:55.620
Hmm.

11:55.620 --> 11:57.670
♪♪

11:57.670 --> 11:59.250
You know, if you ever want
a car of your own,

11:59.250 --> 12:00.500
you're going to have
to find a good job.

12:00.500 --> 12:02.210
And the only way to do that
is college.

12:02.210 --> 12:03.210
[ Sighs ]

12:03.210 --> 12:05.120
I saw on YouTube that
in the future,

12:05.120 --> 12:07.210
all jobs are going
to be done by robots.

12:07.210 --> 12:09.580
So why bother going into debt
for a worthless degree?

12:09.580 --> 12:12.040
Maybe a robot can do some jobs,
but not all jobs.

12:12.040 --> 12:13.420
Not my job.
Yes, your job.

12:13.420 --> 12:14.920
[ Scoffs ]
Your job already.

12:14.920 --> 12:16.960
A robot cannot be
a professor.

12:16.960 --> 12:19.290
Remember you were so proud
that the university

12:19.290 --> 12:20.960
recorded your lectures
to show online?

12:20.960 --> 12:22.790
Mm.
Think about it.

12:22.790 --> 12:24.920
Now they can
stream them forever.

12:24.920 --> 12:26.460
[ Chuckles ] Face it.

12:26.460 --> 12:29.790
Robot you is putting real you
out of a job.

12:31.500 --> 12:32.620
[ Tires pop ]
Oh!

12:32.620 --> 12:35.330
Fudge it!

12:35.330 --> 12:40.460
♪♪

12:40.460 --> 12:43.290
A robot wouldn't have
done that.

12:43.290 --> 12:46.920
[ Classical music playing ]

12:51.920 --> 12:54.330
Beautiful work, everyone.

12:54.330 --> 12:57.330
Nice form.

12:57.330 --> 12:59.420
Oliver,
round out your arms.

12:59.420 --> 13:01.670
Lift your chest.

13:01.670 --> 13:03.000
Oh, forget it.

13:03.000 --> 13:05.960
You look like a lollipop
having a seizure.

13:05.960 --> 13:07.290
Okay, class.
[ Claps ]

13:07.290 --> 13:08.500
Pliés.

13:10.620 --> 13:13.580
Nicely done, everyone,
except Oliver.

13:13.580 --> 13:17.170
Okay, that's it for today.

13:17.170 --> 13:18.580
[ Music stops ]

13:24.080 --> 13:25.790
Oliver, honey,
you really have been

13:25.790 --> 13:27.330
working your butt off.

13:27.330 --> 13:28.750
I told you.

13:28.750 --> 13:30.080
What do you think I'm doing
in my room every night

13:30.080 --> 13:32.120
with the door closed?

13:32.120 --> 13:33.000
Mom!

13:33.000 --> 13:35.170
You're 13.
I don't know.

13:35.170 --> 13:36.620
I'm practicing.

13:36.620 --> 13:38.750
First, I was just doing it
to get into Harvard,

13:38.750 --> 13:40.750
but now...

13:40.750 --> 13:42.540
I kinda love it.

13:42.540 --> 13:43.920
You're like
a "Bachelor" contestant

13:43.920 --> 13:46.380
who goes on the show for fame,
but by the end...

13:46.380 --> 13:48.420
is in it
for the right reasons.

13:50.460 --> 13:52.960
She's really hard
on you, huh?

13:52.960 --> 13:54.210
I've been telling you.

13:54.210 --> 13:55.330
She has it in for me.

13:55.330 --> 13:56.790
I'm sorry.

13:56.790 --> 13:59.080
I feel so bad
for not believing you.

13:59.080 --> 14:00.210
It's okay, Mom.

14:00.210 --> 14:03.250
No, it's not.

14:03.250 --> 14:05.420
I'm gonna go talk to her.

14:05.420 --> 14:07.210
Even though keeping him
in ballet will officially be

14:07.210 --> 14:08.960
the end of my master plan.

14:08.960 --> 14:10.330
Watch out.
She's horrible.

14:10.330 --> 14:12.790
No one's more horrible
than your mother!

14:12.790 --> 14:14.080
Hi.

14:14.080 --> 14:15.960
I'm Katie Otto,
Oliver's mom.

14:18.580 --> 14:19.830
Okay.

14:19.830 --> 14:21.420
I was watching,
and it looks like

14:21.420 --> 14:23.540
you're being harder on him
than anyone else.

14:23.540 --> 14:25.330
Are you doing that thing
where you challenge him

14:25.330 --> 14:27.210
so he rises
to his potential?

14:27.210 --> 14:29.420
No, that's not
what I'm doing.

14:29.420 --> 14:31.880
He doesn't have
what it takes.

14:31.880 --> 14:34.420
I saw him,
and he does have it.

14:34.420 --> 14:36.920
I'm not wasting my time
on some spoiled kid.

14:36.920 --> 14:38.670
If you would have said
"arrogant" and "obnoxious,"

14:38.670 --> 14:40.830
you would have been right,
but he's not spoiled.

14:40.830 --> 14:44.580
Maybe he is just too good
for you and your stupid class.

14:44.580 --> 14:46.040
[ Exhales ]

14:47.670 --> 14:48.830
Did you just bump me?

14:48.830 --> 14:50.210
[ Chuckles ]

14:50.210 --> 14:51.880
Don't make me go "Black Swan"
on you.

14:51.880 --> 14:52.960
What, you're gonna
go crazy

14:52.960 --> 14:54.580
and stab yourself
with a piece of glass?

14:54.580 --> 14:55.880
Is that what happens?
I didn't see the movie.

14:55.880 --> 14:57.460
It's always showing
at a bad time.

14:57.460 --> 15:00.330
Class is over.

15:00.330 --> 15:03.620
You need to go.

15:03.620 --> 15:05.830
[ Laughs ]

15:05.830 --> 15:08.500
You clearly do not have a sense
of size and proportion.

15:08.500 --> 15:09.620
[ Laughs ]

15:09.620 --> 15:11.500
Don't let the leotard
fool you, honey.

15:11.500 --> 15:19.170
♪♪

15:22.210 --> 15:23.330
[ Sighs ]
I really thought I had you

15:23.330 --> 15:25.170
until you got me
in that leg-lock.

15:25.170 --> 15:26.790
You have some
powerful thighs.

15:26.790 --> 15:28.210
I like the way
you used your breasts

15:28.210 --> 15:29.580
as a weapon.

15:29.580 --> 15:31.460
Thank you.

15:31.460 --> 15:34.040
I just assumed Oliver was
one stuck-up kid

15:34.040 --> 15:36.380
doing ballet as a dare
or something.

15:36.380 --> 15:40.000
But...now that I've met you,
I know I had him all wrong.

15:40.000 --> 15:43.080
He's not from one
of those good families.

15:43.080 --> 15:45.460
No. He is not.
[ Sighs ]

15:45.460 --> 15:47.880
You know, he does have
some real potential.

15:50.290 --> 15:51.920
I watched "Flashdance"
when he was in my womb,

15:51.920 --> 15:53.580
so I take some credit
for it.

15:53.580 --> 15:55.670
Just because Oliver
is from Westport,

15:55.670 --> 15:59.540
I had all these
preconceived notions about him.

15:59.540 --> 16:02.330
You know...
I've also been told

16:02.330 --> 16:05.380
that I judge people
from Westport.

16:05.380 --> 16:07.170
I suppose I owe him
an apology.

16:07.170 --> 16:09.290
Yeah.

16:09.290 --> 16:12.210
I owe some people
an apology, too.

16:12.210 --> 16:13.920
Sage:
Before we finish up,

16:13.920 --> 16:16.880
I just want to congratulate
this year's volunteers.

16:16.880 --> 16:19.790
Give yourselves a hand!
[ Applause ]

16:19.790 --> 16:23.080
But there's still one more
chairperson position to fill.

16:23.080 --> 16:25.540
Takes place in the spring...

16:27.420 --> 16:29.580
Oh, come on, now.
The Spring Gala's fun!

16:29.580 --> 16:31.540
[ Chuckles ]

16:31.540 --> 16:33.580
The doctors couldn't
definitively link

16:33.580 --> 16:35.710
Stacy Clouser's breakdown
to the --
[ Door opens ]

16:35.710 --> 16:38.670
Oh.

16:38.670 --> 16:41.540
Hi, everyone.

16:43.750 --> 16:47.380
It has been brought
to my attention

16:47.380 --> 16:51.710
that the problem I have
with so many of you...

16:51.710 --> 16:53.880
so many...

16:53.880 --> 16:56.540
is not actually with you.

16:56.540 --> 16:58.960
The problem is with me.

16:58.960 --> 17:00.330
[ Inspirational music plays ]

17:00.330 --> 17:03.040
I mean,
I should not judge you.

17:03.040 --> 17:05.670
Who cares if
you only volunteer

17:05.670 --> 17:08.080
to justify not having jobs
to your rich husbands?

17:08.080 --> 17:09.290
[ Music distorts, stops ]

17:09.290 --> 17:11.120
That came out wrong.

17:11.120 --> 17:13.170
[ Music resumes ]
I'm not saying what you do
at the school

17:13.170 --> 17:16.040
isn't important,
because it is.

17:16.040 --> 17:18.620
Like when you all painted
that mural celebrating

17:18.620 --> 17:20.460
Diversity Day with
all the different ethnicities

17:20.460 --> 17:21.960
that this town doesn't have.

17:21.960 --> 17:23.330
[ Music distorts, stops ]

17:23.330 --> 17:26.380
That sounded judgy.
I heard it.

17:26.380 --> 17:27.460
[ Music resumes ]

17:27.460 --> 17:30.170
This is not going well.

17:30.170 --> 17:32.670
I guess there's only one way
back into their good graces.

17:32.670 --> 17:34.670
I will give back

17:34.670 --> 17:36.250
the diaper purse.

17:36.250 --> 17:37.460
[ Music stops ]

17:40.250 --> 17:42.620
No?

17:42.620 --> 17:44.080
Fine.

17:44.080 --> 17:45.120
I'll chair the Spring Gala.

17:45.120 --> 17:47.830
[ Screams ]
[ Applause ]

17:47.830 --> 17:50.920
This is a good start.
I'm so proud of you, Katie.

17:50.920 --> 17:52.920
[ Laughs ]

17:52.920 --> 17:56.790
This job is going to consume
all your time and energy.

17:56.790 --> 17:59.580
It will hang over your head
the entire year,

17:59.580 --> 18:04.000
keep you up at night,
and, ultimately, destroy you.

18:04.000 --> 18:06.290
I'm so happy.
[ Laughs ]

18:06.290 --> 18:07.540
Stupid says what?

18:07.540 --> 18:09.210
What?
Ha!

18:09.210 --> 18:10.500
It wasn't my best comeback,

18:10.500 --> 18:12.290
but I got to get home
to make dinner.

18:12.290 --> 18:14.790
♪♪

18:14.790 --> 18:16.170
Katie: How was
the driving lesson today?

18:16.170 --> 18:18.290
Apparently, I'm going to be
replaced by a robot

18:18.290 --> 18:19.920
and we need
four new tires.
[ Sighs ]

18:19.920 --> 18:22.080
It doesn't matter
if Taylor drives anyway.

18:22.080 --> 18:24.540
Not only do I have the worst
volunteer job there is

18:24.540 --> 18:26.460
with the promise
of a public nervous breakdown,

18:26.460 --> 18:27.920
but the Spring Gala
will take up

18:27.920 --> 18:29.210
any free time
that I already had.

18:29.210 --> 18:30.580
I'm sorry, honey.

18:30.580 --> 18:32.920
I'm gonna have to become
what I hate the most --

18:32.920 --> 18:34.670
an over-involved,
no-life,

18:34.670 --> 18:37.080
busy-body, idiot
Westport housewife.

18:37.080 --> 18:39.620
Bright side, I'm back on
the recycling committee again.

18:39.620 --> 18:40.960
Congratulations --

18:40.960 --> 18:42.460
bi-weekly meetings
in a school basement

18:42.460 --> 18:43.460
with three janitors.

18:43.460 --> 18:45.580
And Bill Doty.

18:45.580 --> 18:46.580
Let's do this.

18:48.620 --> 18:50.830
Hey, you guys can't come in here
without knocking!

18:50.830 --> 18:52.880
[ Laughs ]
You're adorable.

18:52.880 --> 18:54.120
Go!

18:54.120 --> 18:55.460
Until you come up
with a plan

18:55.460 --> 18:56.830
on what you want to do
after high school,

18:56.830 --> 18:58.580
college is
still the current plan.

18:58.580 --> 19:00.830
And I talked to your teachers,
and you need to be done

19:00.830 --> 19:02.580
with your summer packet
by the week's end.

19:02.580 --> 19:05.460
And if you don't do it,
there's always boarding school.

19:05.460 --> 19:06.580
We all know we can't afford
boarding school --

19:06.580 --> 19:07.620
empty threat!

19:09.290 --> 19:11.420
You guys are being
so unfair!

19:11.420 --> 19:12.210
Ooh.

19:12.210 --> 19:13.210
We're "unfair."

19:13.210 --> 19:14.830
Nice job.
Thank you.

19:14.830 --> 19:16.250
I just have
to face it --

19:16.250 --> 19:18.250
I can't take a step back
from mothering.

19:18.250 --> 19:20.040
I'll just phone in
being a wife.

19:20.040 --> 19:21.210
Understood.
Mm-hmm.

19:21.210 --> 19:23.080
I'll take this one.

19:23.080 --> 19:27.170
Anna-Kat, ponies down.
We need to talk.

19:27.170 --> 19:29.460
I signed up
for volunteering.

19:29.460 --> 19:32.380
You are going to sign up
for an after-school club.

19:32.380 --> 19:34.500
And, FYI,
this is the last time

19:34.500 --> 19:37.750
I negotiate
with an eight-year-old.

19:37.750 --> 19:39.580
Anna-Kat:
That's so unfair!

19:39.580 --> 19:41.210
Ooh, we're two for two.
Mm-hmm.

19:41.210 --> 19:43.420
Let's go
into Oliver's room.

19:43.420 --> 19:44.830
We should probably give him
some warning

19:44.830 --> 19:45.750
before we go in.

19:45.750 --> 19:47.880
[ Both coughing ]

19:47.880 --> 19:49.500
Well, here we are,
at Oliver's room.

19:49.500 --> 19:50.460
Let's go in.
Let's talk to him.

19:50.460 --> 19:51.460
Yeah.

19:51.460 --> 19:54.380
[ Classical music playing ]

20:05.040 --> 20:06.120
[ Music stops ]

20:06.120 --> 20:07.790
Looking good.

20:07.790 --> 20:09.830
Just practicing for the recital
next week.

20:09.830 --> 20:11.750
I've been moved up
to premiere danseur.

20:11.750 --> 20:13.420
Well, that's great.
You know what?

20:13.420 --> 20:15.250
You deserve it.

20:15.250 --> 20:17.620
Thanks for sticking up
for me.

20:19.170 --> 20:20.620
Oh, honey.

20:20.620 --> 20:22.170
[ Chuckles ]

20:22.170 --> 20:25.330
That...
is what I'm here for.

20:25.330 --> 20:31.460
♪♪

20:31.460 --> 20:32.830
Huh.

20:32.830 --> 20:34.790
Who'd have thought today that
our pain-in-the-ass kid

20:34.790 --> 20:36.290
would be our best kid?

20:36.290 --> 20:38.040
What I like most about
being a parent

20:38.040 --> 20:40.420
is that things change
all the time.
Mm.

20:40.420 --> 20:42.380
That's not true.
I just want all this to be over.

20:42.380 --> 20:44.920
♪♪

20:49.670 --> 20:51.710
I know the Spring Gala has
this reputation for being awful,

20:51.710 --> 20:52.380
but come on,

20:52.380 --> 20:54.040
how bad can it really be?

20:54.040 --> 20:55.380
I'm sure they're exaggerating

20:55.380 --> 20:57.210
this whole Stacy Clouser thing.

20:57.210 --> 20:58.250
Shrimp!

20:58.250 --> 20:59.250
Shrimp!

20:59.250 --> 21:00.420
There's not enough shrimp!

21:00.420 --> 21:01.540
Oh!
It's okay.

21:01.540 --> 21:02.750
You call yourself...
Honey, I know.

21:02.750 --> 21:04.790
...a Better-Business-
accredited vendor?

21:04.790 --> 21:05.830
You're garbage!!

21:05.830 --> 21:08.460
I'll be fine.

21:08.460 --> 21:09.290
Right?

21:09.290 --> 21:10.460
♪♪
